{
  "_comment": "Committed inventory of the eval catalog: suite directory -> sorted case ids. EvalCatalogManifestTests regenerates this map from Suites/**/*.json on every CI run and fails on ANY drift — so deleting, renaming, or re-homing a case is always a deliberate, reviewable diff here rather than a silent catalog change (the decode smokes only assert floor counts, which additions never break but deletions could slip past). When the test fails it writes the freshly computed manifest to a temp path and prints it; copy that file over this one after confirming the catalog change is intentional. The test also enforces globally unique case ids and zero decode failures across the catalog.",
